The paper discusses the application of the information bottleneck principle in the analysis of deep models, particularly in the context of generative models such as VAE and GAN. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Given the focus on deep generative models, cs.LG is the most likely category, followed by cs.IT and cs.CV. The paper also discusses the interpretability of generative models, which is a topic of interest in cs.AI and cs.NE.
